<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n53109u"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53109u">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53109u"> 109(u)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Eisberg&apos;s d</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">MENAGERIE <p class="set">First comes the African Polar Bear, oft called the <mark>Iceberg&apos;s daughter</mark>, <br>She&apos;s been known to eat three tubs of ice, then call for soda water; <br>She wades in the water up to her knees, not fearing any harm, <br>And you may grumble all you please, and she don&apos;t care a &ldquo;darn.&rdquo;</p> <small> Sigmund Spaeth, <a name="REAW1" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#REAW1"><cite title="source">Read 'Em and Weep</cite></a> (1935) 76</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: German <i>Eisberg</i>. </mm> </dd></dl>
